<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-11 00:34 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Comets 73, Starzz 71  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- Guard Janeth Arcain picked up a wayward
rebound and sank a 16-foot jumper with one second to play, lifting
the Houston Comets to a 73-71 WNBA victory over the Utah Starzz on
Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Utah tied the game with nine seconds to play as rookie point
guard Stacy Frese swished a 3-pointer. But after a Houston timeout,
Arcain converted Cynthia Cooper's missed driving layup into a
game-winner.
</P>
<P>
   Sheryl Swoopes led Houston (6-1) with 22 points, nearly three
shy of her 24.8-point average, second-highest in the league. Tina
Thompson added 18 points and four blocks, while holding Olympian
Natalie Williams in check.
</P>
<P>
   Williams led Utah with 17 points and nine rebounds, but scored
just 13 while playing against Thompson. Adrienne Goodson added 15
points for the Starzz.
</P>
<P>
   Utah (3-3) is 1-12 against the Comets in four seasons.
</P>
<P>
   Utah held a 35-26 rebounding advantage and rallied from a
12-point first-half deficit to go up 64-58 in the second half, when
there were six lead changes. But the Starzz's 18 turnovers, six by
Williams led to 15 Comets points.
</P>
<P>
   The teams meet again Monday night in Houston.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
