<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-11 00:57 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dodgers 7, Athletics 2  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Eric Karros tied the Los Angeles career home
run record and Shawn Green also homered as the Los Angeles Dodgers
beat the Oakland Athletics 7-2 on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Kevin Brown (5-2) recorded his third complete game of the season
with a seven-hitter, including Jason Giambi's RBI single in the
sixth inning and Eric Chavez's solo homer in the seventh.
</P>
<P>
   The right-hander, who has not allowed more than three earned
runs in any of his 12 outings this year, went the distance for the
eighth time in 47 starts with the Dodgers.
</P>
<P>
   Karros's sixth-inning, solo homer was his 17th of the season and
228th of his career, tying Ron Cey's record for Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   Karros, who has spent his entire career with the Dodgers, drove
a 1-1 pitch from reliever Scott Service into the lower seats in the
left-field corner to make it 7-1.
</P>
<P>
   Omar Olivares (3-8) allowed three runs in the first inning and
lost his fifth straight start. Olivares, tied for the most losses
in the majors, allowed six runs and nine hits in six innings.
</P>
<P>
   F.P. Santangelo led off the first with a single, Mark
Grudzielanek doubled inside first base and Gary Sheffield scored
both runners with a double off the fence in right-center. Green
then looped a broken-bat RBI double inside the left-field line.
</P>
<P>
   The Dodgers made it 4-0 in the third on a two-out walk to Chad
Kreuter and singles by Alex Cora and Brown, who leads Dodgers
pitchers with three RBIs in 24 at-bats.
</P>
<P>
   Olivares walked Sheffield with one out in the fourth before
surrendering Green's 11th homer, a towering drive to right-center
that made it 6-0.
</P>
<P>
   Oakland was the only American League team Green did not homer
against last season, when he hit a career-high 42 for Toronto.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Karros needed 4,669 career at-bats to reach 228 homers, 547
fewer than Cey. ... Including Olivares' third-inning single,
Oakland pitchers are 4-for-51 at the plate since interleague play
began in 1997. ... Giambi was hit by a pitch in the first inning,
he became the first batter plunked by Brown this season and the
37th by Dodger pitchers -- the most in the majors.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-06-11-00 0057 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
