<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rapids 1, Galaxy 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER (AP) -- Junior Agogo's goal in sudden-death overtime gave
the Colorado Rapids a 1-0 victory Saturday over the Los Angeles
Galaxy at Mile High Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   After a scoreless 94 minutes, Agogo capitalized on a turnover by
Galaxy defender Paul Caligiuri in his own box. Agogo collected
Caligiuri's errant clearance and fired a shot that deflected off
defender Robin Fraser and past Galaxy goalkeeper Kevin Hartman.
</P>
<P>
   The goal for Agogo was his team-leading seventh of the season
and his league-leading fourth game-winner.
</P>
<P>
   Rapids defender Chris Martinez held forward Luis Hernandez to
one shot on the goal. Colorado also held the Galaxy to no shots on
goal in the first half.
</P>
</TEXT>
