<HEADLINE> 7-year-old saves baby sitter from drowning  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ALPINE, N.J. (AP) - She was supposed to be protecting the child,
but a 23-year-old New York woman found herself being rescued from
drowning by a 7-year-old.
</P>
<P>
   Elia Luna of Queens was watching Mikella Goldman as the two were
in a backyard pool Saturday when the woman started struggling.
</P>
<P>
   ''She was doing backstrokes not really well, and then she
floated down in the water,'' the girl said.
</P>
<P>
   Her father, Richard Goldman, said he was reading a newspaper
when he looked up and saw Mikella appear in the shallow section,
pulling the floating Luna, who was motionless and face down, by the
foot.
</P>
<P>
   He pulled Luna from the pool, saw she wasn't breathing, and gave
her mouth-to-mouth resuscitation as Mikella ran inside the house
and called 911.
</P>
<P>
   Luna regained consciousness and was taken to Englewood Hospital
and Medical Center, where she was recovering. She said she did not
know why she lost consciousness.
</P>
<P>
   Mikella said she was upset to see Luna taken away in an
ambulance.
</P>
<P>
   ''I was sad because she's my favorite babysitter,'' she said.
</P>
</TEXT>
