<HEADLINE> Asbury Park, Neptune teens clash in post-party fight  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ASBURY PARK, N.J. (AP) - About ten people were charged with
disorderly conduct in a street fight involving 250 teens that began
as people cursing at each other and escalated into bottle- and
rock-throwing.
</P>
<P>
   Several police officers suffered minor injuries in the Friday
night clash between city teens and teens from Neptune, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Many of the people in the fight had just left a Sweet 16 party
at Veterans of Foreign Wars Post 2639 on Corlies Avenue in Neptune,
police said. The teens met on a street in Asbury Park and began
fighting shortly before 11:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   ''The fight was Asbury against Neptune,'' Asbury Park police
Sgt. Chris Van Buren told the Asbury Park Press of Neptune for
Sunday's editions.
</P>
<P>
   ''You could hear people in the crowd saying, 'Hey those ----
from Asbury,' and then you heard them answering, 'Those ---- kids
from Neptune,''' Van Buren said.
</P>
<P>
   It took about 25 police officers to break up the fight. Police
said they had a hard time breaking up the fight, adding other
fights were reported in other parts of the city until 2 a.m.
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Those under arrest were released after being charged. Police
didn't identify the people who were arrested but said some were
juveniles and all were males from either Asbury Park or Neptune.
</P>
</TEXT>
