<HEADLINE> One dead, one injured in botched restaurant robbery  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   SUMTER, S.C. (AP) - One man is dead and another is in critical
condition after a restaurant robbery ended in gunfire.
</P>
<P>
   Guang Liang Lin, 28, was killed Saturday night by a single
gunshot wound to the chest, Police Chief Harold Johnson said. A
nursing supervisor said Tong Lin, 27, was in critical condition
Sunday at Palmetto Richland Memorial Hospital, where he was being
treated for multiple gunshot wounds.
</P>
<P>
   It was unclear whether the victims were related.
</P>
<P>
   Police said two men with guns went into China Buffet and
demanded money. One of the robbers shot Guang Liang Lin after Tong
Lin began arguing with the robbers.
</P>
<P>
   Police said Sunday they had not identified any suspects, but
Johnson said restaurant customers were able to provide a vague
description of the gunmen.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson said four other businesses in the area had been robbed
in the last two months.
</P>
<P>
   ''I think we have a couple of people who are coming into town
and doing these robberies,'' Johnson said. ''We are going to do our
best to catch them and put them in prison.''
</P>
<P>
   Sumter County Coroner Verna Moore was trying to locate Guang
Liang Lin's family. She said Guang Liang Lin carried a New Jersey
driver's license, and that it appeared he had no relatives in South
Carolina.
</P>
</TEXT>
