<HEADLINE> Hair Spurs Boy's Disqualification  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MANAGUA, Nicaragua (AP) -- Theo Sullow's victory in the first leg
of a national math competition won't get him to the next round
unless he cuts his hair, an official said.
</P>
<P>
   Mercedes Garcia Guevara disqualified the 12-year-old boy from
the second round of Nicaragua's Math Olympics because his ''weird
hairdo'' -- long and parted down the middle -- did not meet the
requirements of having a ''personal presentation of a student.''
</P>
<P>
   Garcia Guevara is the government representative in Esteli, where
the national competition is being held. Esteli is 90 miles north of
Managua.
</P>
<P>
   Students have marched in the streets to protest the
disqualification. And the boy's parents, originally from Germany,
said they were appealing the decision, and would ask the German
Embassy for help if they received no response.
