<HEADLINE> Woman in town for Americade killed in motorcycle-car collision  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   LAKE GEORGE, N.Y. (AP) - A Connecticut woman was killed and her
husband injured Saturday when their motorcycles collided with a car
that swerved into oncoming traffic on a state highway.
</P>
<P>
   Doris C. Hamann, 52, of Waterbury was thrown from her 1997
Harley-Davidson when she collided head-on with an Oldsmobile
operated by a 74-year-old Saratoga County woman. She was pronounced
dead at a local hospital. Richard C. Hamann, her husband, was
thrown from his 1985 Honda motorcycle in the same accident. He was
treated and released from the hospital after complaining of a back
injury.
</P>
