   The couple was among the thousands of motorcyclists
participating in the Americade - touted as the world's largest
rally of its kind. Two motorcyclists died in separate accidents
while attending the event last year. In 1998, an Australian
attending the event died.
</P>
<P>
   Muriel Schwarz, the driver of the Oldsmobile, was treated and
released for a wrist injury. She was ticketed for failure to keep
right. Police say an investigation is under way.
</P>
