By The Associated Press	   Partly cloudy conditions are expected in central and
eastern New
York Monday. The National Weather Service forecast calls for a
chance of showers and possible thunderstorm in southeast counties.
High temperatures should range from the 60s to 70. In the evening,
clear to cloudy conditions are forecast across the state with lows
ranging from 45 to 55.
