a number of timely shots from Travis Best helped the Indiana Pacers defeat the
Los Angeles Lakers 100-91 tonight. Indiana took a double-digit lead early, went
ahead by as many as 18 points and held off the Lakers' rally in the fourth to
cut their deficit to 2-1 in the series. Game four is Wednesday night at Indiana.
AP NewsBrief by RICHARD A. SOMMA 
