<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-11 23:01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mets-Yankees Postponed By Rain  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The final game of the Mets-Yankees Subway Series
was rained out Sunday night before the teams could complete the
third inning.
</P>
<P>
   The Yankees led 1-0 when the game was stopped with one out in
the bottom of the third. Lightning flashed just outside Yankee
Stadium and there was a big clap of thunder before the umpires
called for the tarp to be put on the field.
</P>
<P>
   The rain got heavier during the delay and the game was called
after a wait of 1 hour, 31 minutes, sending home an unhappy sellout
crowd. No makeup date was immediately announced.
</P>
<P>
   The teams have only one common off-day the rest of the season,
Aug. 31. The Mets end a homestand the day before and head to St.
Louis on Sept. 1. The Yankees end a West Coast trip on Aug. 30. The
teams also could play on July 12, the day after the All-Star game.
</P>
<P>
   David Cone, who struggled with a 1-6 record and 6.49 ERA
entering the game, didn't allow a hit through three innings. He
walked two and struck out four.
</P>
<P>
   Pitching on five days rest -- one more than usual -- Cone once
again looked dominant. He got Edgardo Alfonzo to wave at a slider
to end the first inning, and froze Mike Piazza on an inside
fastball to open the second. Only one ball was hit to the outfield,
a harmless fly to right by Todd Zeile.
</P>
<P>
   Over the past two seasons, Cone has excelled with extra rest. He
is 10-7 with a 2.70 ERA with at least five days between starts, and
3-8 with a 6.31 ERA with four days off.
</P>
<P>
   He has struggled especially since pitching a perfect game last
July 18 against Montreal, losing 11 of 14 decisions.
</P>
<P>
   The Yankees scored their only run in the second inning against
Mike Hampton, making his first career start at Yankee Stadium.
Shane Spencer walked to lead off the inning, went to third on Scott
Brosius' hit-and-run single and scored on a sacrifice fly by Chris
Turner.
</P>
<P>
   The teams split the first two games of the series and the
Yankees lead the Subway Series 8-6. They will meet again July 7-9
at Shea Stadium.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Game 3 of the NBA Finals between Indiana and Los Angeles
was shown on the scoreboard during the rain delay. ... The Yankees
start a series Monday against Boston, with Orlando Hernandez
pitching against Brian Rose. ... The Mets are off Monday before
playing a two-game set against the Cubs at Wrigley Field starting
Tuesday. ... Bernie Williams and Paul O'Neill were the only Yankees
in the starting lineup to face Hampton before Sunday. ... Hampton's
first career win came against the Yankees in relief for Seattle on
April 23, 1993. This was his first start against the Yankees. ...
Yankees 2B Chuck Knoblauch, who has not played since last Sunday
because of a sore left forearm, took BP but did not play.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-06-11-00 2301 </TRAILER>
