<HEADLINE> Reports: Two killed, several injured in boat crash  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   OCEAN CITY, N.J. (AP) - Two people were killed and several
others were injured when a speed boat and pleasure boat collided
Sunday evening, according to broadcast reports.
</P>
<P>
   State Police were investigating the crash, which happened around
7 p.m. They released no information.
</P>
<P>
   FOX-TV in Philadelphia reported that the high-speed boat
collided with the pleasure boat in the Intracoastal Waterway off
Ocean City.
</P>
<P>
   WPVI-TV in Philadelphia reported that the driver and lone
passenger on the 28-foot speed boat were killed.
</P>
<P>
   Ten people were on the other boat, a 29-foot cabin cruiser out
for a graduation party. All were ejected and at least five were
taken to area hospitals, the station reported.
</P>
<P>
   The station reported that excessive speed is being investigated
as a possible cause.
</P>
<P>
   Both boats were to be taken to a nearby U.S. Coast Guard station
for further investigation.
