<HEADLINE> NY Boy Killed Playing Baseball  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CENTEREACH, N.Y. (AP) -- A 7-year-old boy playing baseball in his
backyard died after the ball struck him in the chest.
</P>
<P>
   Ryan Blanco and his brother, whose name and age were withheld,
were playing outside their Long Island home Sunday night while
their parents were inside, police said.
</P>
<P>
   His brother, who was about the same age, hit the baseball and it
struck Ryan, who immediately collapsed, police said.
</P>
<P>
   A neighbor started CPR, and paramedics continued it on the way
to University Medical Center at Stony Brook, but the boy was
pronounced dead shortly after arrival.
</P>
<P>
   An autopsy was planned to determine the cause of death.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-06-11-00 2359 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
